n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[We're All No One]]\n | prev_year  = 2011\n | title      = I Like \u2013 The Remix\n | year       = 2012\n | next_title = [[Can't Stop Me]]\n | next_year  = 2012\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''I Like (The Remix)'''\" is a song released by American rapper [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] featuring [[Enrique Iglesias]] and [[Afrojack]]. Originally a remix of \"I Like How It Feels\" by Afrojack,<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G_yesVoEKIQ|title=Enrique Iglesias \u2013 I Like How It Feels (Afrojack Remix)|date=17 October 2011|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> it was reworked by DJ Buddha and released as a single instead. The track was later featured as a [[B-side]] track on the CD releases of the Pitbull singles \"[[Get It Started]]\" and \"[[Don't Stop the Party (Pitbull song)|Don't Stop the Party]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/Get-Started-Pitbull-Featuring-Shakira/dp/B008S0BMRY|title=Get It Started|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/Dont-Stop-Party-feat-TJR/dp/B009DBKIZY|title=Don't Stop the Party feat. TJR \u2013 Pitbull: Amazon.de: Musik|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe song was selected as the official song of [[Miss USA 2012]]. This marks the second song by Pitbull to be used for a beauty pageant (after \"Took My Love\", a track from his album ''[[Planet Pit]]'', which served as the official song of the rival [[Miss America 2012]] pageant).\n\n== Charts and certifications ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! Chart (2011\u201312)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n!scope=row{{singlechart|Australia|26|artist=Enrique Iglesias feat. Pitbull and The WAV.S|song=I Like How It Feels}}\n|-\n!scope=row{{singlechart|Flanders|43|artist=Enrique Iglesias feat. Pitbull and The WAV.S|song=I Like How It Feels}}\n|-\n!scope=row{{singlechart|Wallonia|43|artist=Enrique Iglesias feat. Pitbull and The WAV.S|song=I Like How It Feels}}\n|-\n!scope=row|Canada ([[Canadian Hot 100]])<ref name=\"billboard\