[[Category:Songs written by Bj\u00f6rn Djupstr\u00f6m]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Adam Baptiste]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = I Like How It Feels\n| cover      = Enrique Iglesias I Like How It Feels.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Enrique Iglesias]] featuring [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] and The WAV.s\n| album      = [[Sex and Love]]\n| released   = 10 September 2011\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     = South Point Studios,<br />([[Miami]], [[Florida]])\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Dance-pop]]\n* [[electro house]]\n}}\n| length     = 3:38\n| label      = [[Universal Republic]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Enrique Iglesias]]|[[RedOne]]|[[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]|[[Alex Papaconstantinou|Alex P]]|Adam Baptiste|Bj\u00f6rn Djupstr\u00f6m|Bilal The Chef}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|[[RedOne]]|[[Alex Papaconstantinou|Alex P]]}}\n| chronology = [[Enrique Iglesias]]\n| prev_title = [[Ayer (Enrique Iglesias song)|Ayer]]\n| prev_year  = 2011\n| next_title = [[Naked (Dev and Enrique Iglesias song)|Naked]]\n| next_year  = 2011\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title = [[Pass at Me]]\n | prev_year  = 2011\n | title      = I Like How It Feels\n | year       = 2011\n | next_title = [[Bailando Por El Mundo]]\n | next_year  = 2011\n}}{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = The WAV.s\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title =\n | prev_year  =\n | title      = I Like How It Feels\n | year       = 2011\n | next_title = [[Down for Whatever]]\n | next_year  = 2011\n}}\n{{External music video|{{YouTube|klk8QPcfFYQ|\"I Like How It Feels\"}}}}\n{{Audio sample\n | type        = single\n | file        = Enrique Iglesias - I Like How It Feels.ogg\n | description = \"I Like How It Feels\"\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''I Like How It Feels'''\" is a song by Spanish recording artist [[Enrique Iglesias]]. The song was originally intended to be the lead single from a reissue of Iglesias' album ''[[Euphoria (Enrique Iglesias album)|Euphoria]]'', however, the release was cancelled. The song was later included on the international deluxe edition of his tenth studio album and second bilingual album ''[[Sex and Love]]''. The song also features guest appearance from American rapper [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] and producers The WAV.s. It is produced by Enrique's longtime collaborator [[RedOne]]. It is the third collaboration between Enrique and Pitbull following \"[[I Like It (Enrique Iglesias song)|I Like It]]\" and Pitbull's song \"Come 'n' Go\" off his then latest album, ''[[Planet Pit]]''. The song was released as a digital download in Australia and some European countries on 23 September 2011. The song was released as a [[Music download|digital download]] in the United States on 4 October 2011.<ref name=\"I Like How It Feels\">{{cite web| url=https://www.amazon.com/I-Like-How-It-Feels/dp/B005O29P6E/ref=sr_1_3?ie=UTF8&qid=1316713645&sr=8-3|title=I Like How It Feels|publisher=Amazon.com|accessdate=29 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\n\"I Like How It Feels\" is produced by [[RedOne]] whose has worked with Enrique previously to produce hits such as \"[[Takin' Back My Love]]\", \"[[I Like It (Enrique Iglesias song)|I Like It]]\" and \"[[Dirty Dancer]]\". The song was leaked on the Internet on 8 September 2011 after which it was uploaded to YouTube on 10 September 2011. The video has now received more than 38 million views.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=daLxgKUad-c|title=Enrique Iglesias-IGLESIAS \u2013 I LIKE HOW IT FEELS FEAT. PITBULL & THE WAV.S|publisher=Youtube|accessdate=9 December 2011}}</ref> The video was directed by Enrique Iglesias. The song was released in some European countries in iTunes on 23 September 2011, and in the US and Canada on 4 October 2011.\n\n== Critical reception ==\nThe single generally received positive reviews. Amy Sciarretto from Popcrush gave 3.5 stars (out of 5) and said, \"It\u2019s a simple set of lyrical declarations that celebrate being upbeat and enjoying life. There\u2019s a fair amount of studio treatment on the song, but that\u2019s a given with any epic, expansive pop song in 2011. We wouldn't be surprised if it becomes a staple at NFL stadiums this fall and winter, too.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Sciarretto|first=Amy|url=http://popcrush.com/enrique-iglesias-i-like-how-it-feels-pitbull/|title=ENRIQUE IGLESIAS 'I LIKE HOW IT FEELS' FEAT. PITBULL \u2013 SONG REVIEW|publisher=Popcrush|accessdate=15 September 2011}}</ref> Meena Rupani from Desihits said,\" The upbeat track is sure to be on repeat just like their other collaboration tracks have been. It seems Enrique Iglesias and Pitbull can do no wrong when they come together on a song.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Rupani|first=Meena|url=http://www.desihits.com/news/view/enrique-iglesias-and-pitbull-drop-i-like-how-it-feels-20110912|publisher=Desihits|title=Enrique Iglesias and Pitbull Drop 'I Like How it Feels'|date=9 December 2011|accessdate=13 September 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120102131611/http://www.desihits.com/news/view/enrique-iglesias-and-pitbull-drop-i-like-how-it-feels-20110912|archive-date=2 January 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref> Robbie Daw from Idolator said,\"Enrique\u2019s new RedOne-produced song has all the musical makings of an anthem, while the singer himself actually packs more of a soulful, emotional punch with his vocals than we've heard on recent singles like \u201cDirty Dancer,\u201d \u201cI Like It\u201d and \u201cTonight (I\u2019m Lovin\u2019 You).\u201d<ref>{{cite web |last=Daw|first=Robbie|url=http://idolator.com/6007132/enrique-iglesias-pitbull-i-like-how-it-feels|title=Enrique Iglesias & Pitbull Whistle Through New Single \"I Like How It Feels\"|publisher=Idolator|accessdate=20 September 2011}}</ref>\n\nLewis Corner from Digital Spy gave the song 4 stars (out of 5) saying, \"Enrique continues to channel the au courrant synths and chunky Euro beats combo that has kept him afloat over the past year. \"It's my time, it's my life, I can do what I like/ For the price of a smile, I gotta take it to right,\" he certifies over a carnival cabaret of Rio de Janeiro proportions \u2013 and with another chart-friendly anthem under his belt, he certainly has reason to celebrate.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a348967/enrique-iglesias-ft-pitbull-i-like-how-it-feels-single-review.html|publisher=Digital Spy|title=Enrique Iglesias ft. Pitbull: 'I Like How It Feels' \u2013 Single review|accessdate=21 November 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Chart performance ==\n[[File:Enrique Iglesias and Pitbull 2015.jpg|thumb|Enrique Iglesias performing with Pitbull in 2015]]\nOn the week of 29 September 2011 the song debuted at number 97 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] chart.<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web |url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=enrique iglesias|chart=all}}|title=Enrique Iglesias|publisher=Billboard|accessdate=29 September 2011}}</ref> It marks Enrique's 8th entry on this chart. It later peaked to #11 on the chart. It also debuted at number 47 on the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA]] charts on the week of 3 October 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/pages/charts_display.asp?chart=1U50 |title=ARIA Top 50 singles chart |publisher=ARIA |access-date=10 March 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100917080655/http://ariacharts.com.au/pages/charts_display.asp?chart=1U50 |archive-date=17 September 2010 }}</ref> Since then, it has managed to peak to #26. On the same day it debuted on 29 on New Zealand's [[RIANZ]] chart, peaking to #19.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://charts.nz/showitem.asp?interpret=Enrique+Iglesias+feat.+Pitbull+and+The+WAV.s&titel=I+Like+How+It+Feels&cat=s|title=ENRIQUE IGLESIAS FEAT. PITBULL AND THE WAV.S \u2013 I LIKE HOW IT FEELS (SONG)|publisher=RIANZ|accessdate=10 October 2011}}</ref> It debuted at #76 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] songs chart. However, due to low sales & low airplay count, it fell out of Hot 100 the following week. It was generally overlooked by US radio. It re-entered the chart at #74 following Enrique's performance of this song on [[American Music Awards of 2011]] & 'The Cowboys Red-Cattle Campaign'.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/week-ending-nov-27-2011-songs-record-rihanna-014630174.html|publisher=Yahoo Chart Watch|title=Week Ending Nov. 27, 2011. Songs: The Record Rihanna Would Like To Shed|date=30 November 2011}}</ref>  It debuted at #40 on the US [[Pop Songs]] chart on the week of 29 October.<ref name=\"chartbeat\">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/column/chartbeat#/column/chartbeat/chart-highlights-katy-perry-debuts-on-pop-1005416612.story|title=Chart Highlights: Katy Perry Debuts On Pop Songs, Lady Gaga Leads Dance/Club Play Songs|work=Billboard.com|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|date=17 October 2011|accessdate=17 October 2011}}</ref> It peaked up to #39. The song topped the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs]], becoming Enrique's 10th #1 on that chart, listing Enrique in the top 10 Dance/Club Artists of all time.\n\n== Use in media ==\n*The song was used in a 2012 Australian commercial for [[Toyota Yaris]].{{citation needed|date=March 2012}}\n*The song was used as part of the Australian [[Seven Network]]'s promo for the [[2012 AFL season]] and its expanded coverage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wp2m9LZgPaQ|title=AFL on 7 in 2012 Long Promo|publisher=MCMedia|work=[[YouTube]]|date=4 March 2012|accessdate=27 December 2015}}</ref>\n*The song was performed by the three remaining finalists on [[The X Factor (Australia season 3)]]\n*The Argentinian [[reality show]] ''So\u00f1ando por Cantar'' uses this song as their theme song, which led the song to great popularity in the country.\n\n== Music video ==\nThe music video for this single premiered on Friday 30 September 2011 via his official website and Vevo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.enriqueiglesias.com/profiles/blogs/i-like-how-it-feels-premiere-is-tomorrow-friday|title=I LIKE HOW IT FEELS PREMIERE IS TOMORROW (FRIDAY)|publisher=enriqueiglesias.com|accessdate=29 September 2011}}</ref> The video is directed by Enrique himself & features guest appearance from stars including singers [[Juanes]], [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]], [[Nicole Scherzinger]], [[Nayer]], actors [[Eva Longoria]], [[Ken Jeong]], [[George Lopez]] and tennis player [[Serena Williams]]. The video starts with Enrique playing on a beach with his dog. The video proceeds with some clips of Enrique's Euphoria tour, night out parties, backstage banter and outdoor videos. The video depicts Enrique flying around Miami beach, playing Baseball with small children, riding speed-boat along with his dog and partying with his friends. Pitbull comes along during his verse also seen partying with Enrique. Ken Jeong is shown writing the song and also dancing it. The video ends with credits to all involved.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=klk8QPcfFYQ|publisher=Youtube|title=I Like How It Feels|date=30 September 2011|accessdate=30 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Live Performance ==\n[[Enrique Iglesias]] performed the song as a medley of two songs on [[American Music Awards of 2011]]. He first sang 'I Like How It Feels' with Choir & then broke into [[Tonight (I'm Lovin' You)]] with guest rap from [[Ludacris]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://popcrush.com/enrique-iglesias-choir-ludacris-i-like-how-it-feels-and-tonight-im-loving-you-2011-american-music-awards/|title=ENRIQUE IGLESIAS GETS ASSIST FROM A CHOIR + LUDACRIS AT 2011 AMERICAN MUSIC AWARDS|publisher=Pop Crush|date=20 November 2011}}</ref> He also performed the song at 'Salvation Army Red Kettle Campaign at Dallas Cowboys Thanksgiving Day Game' as a medley of three songs. He started with 'I Like How It Feels' with guest rap from [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] followed by [[Tonight (I'm Lovin' You)]] & [[I Like It (Enrique Iglesias song)|I Like It]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marketwatch.com/story/enrique-iglesias-kicks-off-salvation-army-red-kettle-campaign-at-dallas-cowboys-thanksgiving-day-game-2011-11-23|title=Enrique Iglesias Kicks Off Salvation Army Red Kettle Campaign at Dallas Cowboys Thanksgiving Day Game|publisher=Market Watch|date=23 November 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = U.S./UK Digital Download\n| title1  = I Like How It Feels\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Enrique Iglesias]]|[[RedOne]]|[[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]|[[Alex Papaconstantinou|Alex P]]|Adam Baptiste|Bj\u00f6rn Djupstr\u00f6m|Bilal The Chef}}\n| length1 = 3:40\n| title2  = I Like How It Feels\n| note2   = Music Video\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Iglesias|RedOne|Pitbull|Alex P|Baptiste|Djupstr\u00f6m|Bilal The Chef}}\n| length2 = 6:18\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = U.K. Digital Download \u2013 The Remixes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/i-like-how-it-feels-remixes/id478133089|title=I Like How It Feels (Remixes) [feat. Pitbull & The WAV.s] \u2013 EP|work=iTunes}}</ref>\n| title1  = I Like How It Feels\n| writer1 = {{hlist|Iglesias|RedOne|Pitbull|Alex P|Baptiste|Djupstr\u00f6m|Bilal The Chef}}\n| length1 = 3:40\n\n| title2  = I Like How It Feels (Benny Benassi Club Mix)\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Iglesias|RedOne|Pitbull|Alex P|Baptiste|Djupstr\u00f6m|Bilal The Chef}}\n| length2 = 5:29\n\n| title3  = I Like How It Feels (DJ Victoria Club Mix)\n| writer3 = {{hlist|Iglesias|RedOne|Pitbull|Alex P|Baptiste|Djupstr\u00f6m|Bilal The Chef}}\n| length3 = 6:00\n\n| title4  = I Like How It Feels (Jump Smokers Club Mix)\n| writer4 = {{hlist|Iglesias|RedOne|Pitbull|Alex P|Baptiste|Djupstr\u00f6m|Bilal The Chef}}\n| length4 = 5:14\n\n| title5  = I Like How It Feels (Sidney Samson Club Mix)\n| writer5 = {{hlist|Iglesias|RedOne|Pitbull|Alex P|Baptiste|Djupstr\u00f6m|Bilal The Chef}}\n| length5 = 6:18\n}}\n\n== Remix ==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = I Like \u2013 The Remix\n| cover      = i-like-remix.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] featuring [[Enrique Iglesias]] and [[Afrojack]]\n| album      =\n| A-side     = {{ubl|\"[[Get It Started]]\"|\"[[Don't Stop the Party (Pitbull song)|Don't Stop the Party]]\"}}\n| released   = 30 January 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/i-like-remix-feat.-enrique/id499296561|title=I Like (The Remix) [feat. Enrique Iglesias & Afrojack] \u2013 Single by Pitbull|publisher=[[iTunes Store|iTunes]]|accessdate=22 February 2012}}</ref>\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Hip house]]|[[electropop]]}}\n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=36}}\n| label      = [[Polo Grounds Music|Polo Grounds]], [[RCA Records|RCA]], Mr. 305\n| writer     = [[Pitbull (rapper)|Armando C. P\u00e9rez]], [[Enrique Iglesias]], [[Afrojack|Nick van de Wall]], [[DJ Buddha|Urales Vargas]], [[RedOne]], [[Alex P]]apaconstantinou, Adam Baptiste, Bj\u00f6rn Djupstr\u00f6m, [[Bilal \"The Chef\" Hajji]]\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* Afrojack\n* DJ Buddha <small>(co.)</small>\n}}\n| chronology = [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]]\n| prev_title = [[Name of Love]]\n| prev_year  = 2012\n| next_title = [[Back in Time (Pitbull song)|Back in Time]]\n| next_year  = 2012\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Enrique Iglesias]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[Naked (Dev and Enrique Iglesias song)|Naked]]\n | prev_year  = 2011\n | title      = I Like \u2013 The Remix\n | year       = 2012\n | next_title = [[Finally Found You]]\n | next_year  = 2012\n}}{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Afrojack]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = [[We're All No One]]\n | prev_year  = 2011\n | title      = I Like \u2013 The Remix\n | year       = 2012\n | next_title = [[Can't Stop Me]]\n | next_year  = 2012\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''I Like (The Remix)'''\" is a song released by American rapper [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]] featuring [[Enrique Iglesias]] and [[Afrojack]]. Originally a remix of \"I Like How It Feels\" by Afrojack,<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G_yesVoEKIQ|title=Enrique Iglesias \u2013 I Like How It Feels (Afrojack Remix)|date=17 October 2011|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> it was reworked by DJ Buddha and released as a single instead. The track was later featured as a [[B-side]] track on the CD releases of the Pitbull singles \"[[Get It Started]]\" and \"[[Don't Stop the Party (Pitbull song)|Don't Stop the Party]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/Get-Started-Pitbull-Featuring-Shakira/dp/B008S0BMRY|title=Get It Started|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/Dont-Stop-Party-feat-TJR/dp/B009DBKIZY|title=Don't Stop the Party feat. TJR \u2013 Pitbull: Amazon.de: Musik|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nThe song was selected as the official song of [[Miss USA 2012]]. This marks the second song by Pitbull to be used for a beauty pageant (after \"Took My Love\", a track from his album ''[[Planet Pit]]'', which served as the official song of the rival [[Miss America 2012]] pageant).\n\n== Charts and certifications ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n! Chart (2011\u201312)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n!scope=row{{singlechart|Australia|26|artist=Enrique Iglesias feat. Pitbull and The WAV.S|song=I Like How It Feels}}\n|-\n!scope=row{{singlechart|Flanders|43|artist=Enrique Iglesias feat. Pitbull and The WAV.S|song=I Like How It Feels}}\n|-\n!scope=row{{singlechart|Wallonia|43|artist=Enrique Iglesias feat. Pitbull and The WAV.S|song=I Like How It Feels}}\n|-\n!scope=row|Canada ([[Canadian Hot 100]])<ref name=\"billboard\" />\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|11\n|-\n!scope=row{{singlechart|Denmark|31|artist=Enrique Iglesias feat. Pitbull and The WAV.S|song=I Like How It Feels}}\n|-\n!scope=row{{sin